“No Standalone Sales” Restriction:
  The Software MAY NOT be sold, sublicensed, or otherwise distributed **on its
  own** (in source or compiled/bundled form) for a fee or other consideration.
  However, you ARE permitted to distribute the Software for free, and you ARE
  permitted to include or embed the Software as part of a larger work (e.g.,
  a commercial application, bundled library package, or SaaS) even if that
  larger work is sold for a fee. In other words:

    • Allowed:
        – Shipping your own app that includes (bundles) this Software as a 
          library/component, even if you charge money for your app.  
        – Forking it on GitHub and redistributing it at no charge.  
        – Internal use by a for-profit company (as long as they don’t charge 
          for “just my code” by itself).  

    • Not Allowed:
        – Publishing “ProjectName vX.Y” on a marketplace (npm, PyPI, Patreon, 
          etc.) as a paid download, without adding any new proprietary code.  
        – Selling source or binaries of just this Software, standalone, for
          a price.  
